description: Wood Wharf is a new mixed use neighbourhood, forming the eastern expansion of Canary Wharf. Allies and Morrison's tour will illustrate how their long term involvement is helping to transform this global financial centre beyond the 9-5.

factsheet.heading: The Tour
paragraphs: Starting at the western entrance of Canary Wharf Jubilee Line station architects, Allies and Morrison, will explain the concepts that underpin the masterplan and trace some key points, from Jubilee Park, Wood Wharf bridge, Harbour Quay and onto Harbord Square Park.

Allies and Morrison's long term involvement in the area involves personalising streets, and introducing parks, homes, schools, shops, cafes and squares - helping to transform this global financial centre, into a place to live, work and play.

location.address: Canary Wharf station, Canary Wharf, E14 5NY

name: Wood Wharf Masterplan Walking Tour
